{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "More testing is required to see if further prompt engineering can increase the effectiveness of the system.",
    "Oliver's interactions were logged with four pieces of information: the timestamp of the interaction, the user query, the retrieved background information, and the LLM\"s response.",
    "These logs were used throughout the term to develop analytics that informed the teaching team.",
    "Specifically, we developed methods to track the relative importance of a given keyword in the queries, much like Google Trends [16], and we used a custom fine-tuned LLM to classify student queries based on their level in the Bloom's Taxonomy [17].",
    "The specifics of each of these analytics is beyond the scope of this paper."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Specifically, we developed methods to track the relative importance of a given keyword in the queries, much like Google Trends [16], and we used a custom fine-tuned LLM to classify student queries based on their level in the Bloom's Taxonomy [17]."
